Note: ================================================================
Note: Bifrost OpenCL Backend
Note: ================================================================
Note: Generates OpenCL C code from Bifrost IR for cross-platform GPUs.
Note: Supports OpenCL 1.2/2.0/3.0 features: kernels, local memory,
Note: work-group operations, atomic operations, and vendor extensions.
Note: ================================================================

Import "../graph/graph.runa" as Graph
Import "../graph/node.runa" as Node
Import "../graph/edge.runa" as Edge
Import "std/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "std/collections/dict.runa" as Dict
Import "std/core/string.runa" as StringMod
Import "std/core/math.runa" as Math

Note: ================================================================
Note: OpenCL Address Space Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant OPENCL_GLOBAL as Integer is 0     Note: __global memory (device DRAM)
Constant OPENCL_LOCAL as Integer is 1      Note: __local memory (on-chip shared)
Constant OPENCL_CONSTANT as Integer is 2   Note: __constant memory (cached, read-only)
Constant OPENCL_PRIVATE as Integer is 3    Note: __private memory (registers)

Note: ================================================================
Note: OpenCL Version Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant OPENCL_1_2 as Integer is 120
Constant OPENCL_2_0 as Integer is 200
Constant OPENCL_3_0 as Integer is 300

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Definitions
Note: ================================================================

Type called "OpenCLKernel":
    name as String                  Note: Kernel function name
    parameters as Integer           Note: List of OpenCLParameter
    body as String                  Note: Kernel body code
    local_memory_bytes as Integer   Note: Local memory requirement
    work_group_size as Integer      Note: Work-group size (threads per group)
    preferred_multiple as Integer   Note: Preferred work-group size multiple
End Type

Type called "OpenCLParameter":
    name as String                  Note: Parameter name
    opencl_type as String           Note: OpenCL type (float*, int, etc.)
    address_space as Integer        Note: OPENCL_* address space
    is_const as Boolean             Note: Whether parameter is const
End Type

Type called "OpenCLDevice":
    platform_id as Integer          Note: Platform identifier
    device_id as Integer            Note: Device identifier
    device_type as Integer          Note: GPU, CPU, ACCELERATOR
    max_compute_units as Integer    Note: Number of compute units
    max_work_group_size as Integer  Note: Maximum work-group size
End Type

Note: ================================================================
Note: Code Generation - Top Level
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_opencl_code" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates complete OpenCL C code from Bifrost graph.

    Output structure:
    1. OpenCL pragmas and version directives
    2. Extension declarations
    3. Type definitions
    4. Helper device functions
    5. Kernel function (__kernel)
    6. Host-side setup comments

    Algorithm:
    - Traverse graph in topological order
    - Emit OpenCL code for each operation
    - Handle address spaces (__global, __local, __constant, __private)
    - Generate kernel signature with proper qualifiers
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate OpenCL version pragmas
    2. Generate extension declarations
    3. Generate type definitions
    4. Generate helper functions
    5. Generate kernel function
    6. Generate host-side setup documentation
    7. Combine into complete OpenCL source
    8. Return OpenCL code string
    @End Implementation

    Let opencl_code be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Add OpenCL version pragma
    Let pragmas be generate_opencl_pragmas(opencl_version)
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, pragmas
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Add extension declarations
    Let extensions be generate_opencl_extensions(opencl_version)
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, extensions
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Add type definitions
    Let typedefs be generate_type_definitions(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, typedefs
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Generate kernel function
    Let kernel be generate_kernel_function(graph, kernel_name, opencl_version)
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, kernel
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, "\n\n"

    Note: Generate host-side setup documentation
    Let setup be generate_host_setup_comments(graph, kernel_name)
    proc append from StringMod with opencl_code, setup

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with opencl_code
End Process

Process called "generate_opencl_pragmas" that takes opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates OpenCL version pragmas and compiler directives.

    OpenCL versions:
    - 1.2: Most compatible, widely supported
    - 2.0: Adds SVM, pipes, generic address space
    - 3.0: Modular extensions, backward compatible
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Determine version string
    2. Generate #pragma OPENCL EXTENSION
    3. Add FP64 support if needed
    4. Return pragma directives
    @End Implementation

    Let pragmas be proc create from StringMod

    If opencl_version is greater than or equal to OPENCL_2_0:
        proc append from StringMod with pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_fp64 : enable\n"
        proc append from StringMod with pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_int64_base_atomics : enable\n"
        proc append from StringMod with pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_int64_extended_atomics : enable\n"
    Otherwise:
        proc append from StringMod with pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_fp64 : enable\n"
    End If

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with pragmas
End Process

Process called "generate_opencl_extensions" that takes opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    Let extensions be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with extensions, "// OpenCL extensions for enhanced functionality\n"

    If opencl_version is greater than or equal to OPENCL_2_0:
        proc append from StringMod with extensions, "// OpenCL 2.0+ features: SVM, generic address space, work-group functions\n"
    Otherwise:
        proc append from StringMod with extensions, "// OpenCL 1.2 compatibility mode\n"
    End If

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with extensions
End Process

Process called "generate_type_definitions" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let typedefs be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Add common type aliases
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "// Type definitions\n"
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "typedef unsigned char uchar;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "typedef unsigned short ushort;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "typedef unsigned int uint;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with typedefs, "typedef unsigned long ulong;\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with typedefs
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Kernel Generation
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_kernel_function" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates OpenCL __kernel function.

    Kernel structure:
    __kernel void kernel_name(__global const float* input,
                             __global float* output,
                             __local float* local_mem,
                             int size) {
        // Work-item index computation
        // Local memory declarations
        // Kernel body (operations)
        // Synchronization (barrier)
    }

    Algorithm:
    - Compute work-group dimensions
    - Generate parameter list with address spaces
    - Generate local memory declarations
    - Generate kernel body from graph
    - Add synchronization points
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate kernel signature with __kernel qualifier
    2. Generate work-item index computation
    3. Generate bounds checking
    4. Generate local memory usage
    5. Traverse graph and emit operations
    6. Add barrier synchronization
    7. Return complete kernel code
    @End Implementation

    Let kernel_code be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Generate kernel signature
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, "__kernel void "
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, kernel_name
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, "(\n"

    Note: Generate parameters
    Let params be generate_kernel_parameters(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, params
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, "\n {\n"

    Note: Generate work-item index computation
    Let work_item_idx be generate_work_item_index_computation()
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, work_item_idx

    Note: Generate local memory declarations
    Let local_mem be generate_local_memory_declarations(graph)
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, local_mem

    Note: Generate kernel body
    Let body be generate_kernel_body(graph, opencl_version)
    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, body

    proc append from StringMod with kernel_code, "}\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with kernel_code
End Process

Process called "generate_kernel_parameters" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates OpenCL kernel parameters with address space qualifiers.

    OpenCL address spaces:
    - __global: Device memory (large, slow)
    - __local: On-chip shared memory (small, fast)
    - __constant: Read-only cached memory
    - __private: Register memory (fastest)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get input and output nodes from graph
    2. Generate __global parameters for buffers
    3. Add __local parameter for shared memory
    4. Add scalar parameters (size)
    5. Return parameter list string
    @End Implementation

    Let params be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Get input and output nodes
    Let all_nodes be proc get_all_nodes from Graph with graph
    Let param_count be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than proc length from List with all_nodes:
        Let node be proc get from List with all_nodes, i
        Let node_type be proc get_node_type from Node with node

        Note: NodeType: Input=1, Output=2
        If node_type equals 1:
            Note: Input parameter
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                proc append from StringMod with params, ",\n"
            End If

            Let opencl_type be map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(proc get_node_output_type from Node with node)
            proc append from StringMod with params, "    __global const "
            proc append from StringMod with params, opencl_type
            proc append from StringMod with params, "* input_"
            proc append from StringMod with params, StringMod.from_int(i )

            Set param_count to param_count plus 1
        End If

        If node_type equals 2:
            Note: Output parameter
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                proc append from StringMod with params, ",\n"
            End If

            Set opencl_type to map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(proc get_node_output_type from Node with node)
            proc append from StringMod with params, "    __global "
            proc append from StringMod with params, opencl_type
            proc append from StringMod with params, "* output_"
            proc append from StringMod with params, StringMod.from_int(i )

            Set param_count to param_count plus 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add local memory parameter
    If param_count is greater than 0:
        proc append from StringMod with params, ",\n"
    End If
    proc append from StringMod with params, "    __local float* local_mem"
    Set param_count to param_count plus 1

    Note: Add size parameter
    If param_count is greater than 0:
        proc append from StringMod with params, ",\n"
    End If
    proc append from StringMod with params, "    int size"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with params
End Process

Process called "generate_work_item_index_computation" that takes nothing returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates OpenCL work-item index computation.

    OpenCL index functions:
    - get_global_id(0): Global work-item index
    - get_local_id(0): Local work-item index within work-group
    - get_group_id(0): Work-group index
    - get_global_size(0): Total number of work-items
    - get_local_size(0): Work-group size
    - get_num_groups(0): Number of work-groups
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate global ID computation
    2. Add bounds checking
    3. Optionally add local ID for shared memory
    4. Return index code
    @End Implementation

    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Compute global work-item index\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    int gid = get_global_id(0 ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    int lid = get_local_id(0 ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    int group_id = get_group_id(0 ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    if (gid >= size return;\n\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

Process called "generate_local_memory_declarations" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates __local memory declarations for work-group shared memory.

    Local memory:
    - Shared by all work-items in a work-group
    - Typically 16-64 KB per compute unit
    - Much faster than global memory
    - Requires barrier() for synchronization
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Analyze graph for local memory needs
    2. Local memory is passed as kernel parameter
    3. Document usage
    4. Return declarations
    @End Implementation

    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Local memory available via kernel parameter\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Typical size: 256 floats = 1024 bytes\n\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

Process called "generate_kernel_body" that takes graph as Integer, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates kernel body by traversing graph in topological order.

    For each operation:
    - Emit OpenCL code for the operation
    - Handle memory accesses with proper address spaces
    - Add synchronization if needed (barrier)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get topological ordering
    2. For each node:
       - Emit OpenCL code for operation
       - Track variable names
    3. Return complete kernel body
    @End Implementation

    Let body be proc create from StringMod

    Note: Get topological sort
    Let sorted_nodes be proc topological_sort from Graph with graph

    Note: Track variable names
    Let var_names be proc create from Dict

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than proc length from List with sorted_nodes:
        Let node be proc get from List with sorted_nodes, i

        Note: Generate code for this operation
        Let op_code be emit_operation_code(node, var_names, i, opencl_version)
        proc append from StringMod with body, op_code

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with body
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Operation Code Emission
Note: ================================================================

Process called "emit_operation_code" that takes node as Integer, var_names as Integer, index as Integer, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Emits OpenCL code for a single operation.

    Operation mapping:
    - Add → result = a + b
    - MatrixMultiply → Manual loop or clBLAS call
    - ReLU → result = max(0.0f, input)
    - Load/Store → memory access with coalescing
    - Atomic → atomic_add, atomic_max, etc.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get operation kind
    2. Get input variables
    3. Emit appropriate OpenCL code
    4. Register output variable
    5. Return code string
    @End Implementation

    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    Let op_kind be proc get_node_opkind from Node with node

    Note: Get result variable name
    Let result_var be proc create from StringMod
    proc append from StringMod with result_var, "var_"
    proc append from StringMod with result_var, StringMod.from_int(index )
    Let result_var_name be proc to_string from StringMod with result_var

    Note: Register variable
    proc set from Dict with var_names, node, result_var_name

    Note: Get OpenCL type
    Let output_type be proc get_node_output_type from Node with node
    Let opencl_type be map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(output_type)

    Note: Emit operation based on OpKind
    Note: Add=0, Subtract=1, Multiply=2, Divide=3
    If op_kind equals 0:
        Note: Add operation
        Let inputs be proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " + "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind equals 1:
        Note: Subtract operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " - "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind equals 2:
        Note: Multiply operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " * "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind equals 3:
        Note: Divide operation
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " / "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Modulo=4
    If op_kind equals 4:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " % "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: ReLU=20
    If op_kind equals 20:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = max(0.0f, "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Sigmoid=21
    If op_kind equals 21:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = 1.0f / (1.0f + exp(-"
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " );\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Tanh=22
    If op_kind equals 22:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = tanh("
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Exp=30
    If op_kind equals 30:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = exp("
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Log=31
    If op_kind equals 31:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = log("
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Sqrt=32
    If op_kind equals 32:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = sqrt("
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Pow=33
    If op_kind equals 33:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = pow("
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ", "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Sin=34
    If op_kind equals 34:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = sin("
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Cos=35
    If op_kind equals 35:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = cos("
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: MatrixMultiply=40
    If op_kind equals 40:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Matrix multiply - using clBLAS in production\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " * "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Reduce operations
    Note: ReduceSum=50, ReduceMax=51, ReduceMin=52
    If op_kind equals 50:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Reduction - sum (requires work-group cooperation \n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    local_mem[lid] = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    barrier(CLK_LOCAL_MEM_FENCE ;\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = local_mem[0];\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind equals 51:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Reduction - max\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    local_mem[lid] = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    barrier(CLK_LOCAL_MEM_FENCE ;\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = local_mem[0];\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind equals 52:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Reduction - min\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    local_mem[lid] = "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ";\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    barrier(CLK_LOCAL_MEM_FENCE ;\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = local_mem[0];\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Atomic operations
    Note: AtomicAdd=60, AtomicMax=61, AtomicMin=62
    If op_kind equals 60:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Atomic add\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = atomic_add(&"
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ", "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind equals 61:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Atomic max\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = atomic_max(&"
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ", "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    If op_kind equals 62:
        Set inputs to proc get_node_inputs from Node with node
        Set input1_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Set input2_var to get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        proc append from StringMod with code, "    // Atomic min\n"
        proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
        proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
        proc append from StringMod with code, " "
        proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
        proc append from StringMod with code, " = atomic_min(&"
        proc append from StringMod with code, input1_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, ", "
        proc append from StringMod with code, input2_var
        proc append from StringMod with code, " ;\n"

        Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
    End If

    Note: Generic operation
    proc append from StringMod with code, "    "
    proc append from StringMod with code, opencl_type
    proc append from StringMod with code, " "
    proc append from StringMod with code, result_var_name
    proc append from StringMod with code, " = 0.0f; // Operation "
    proc append from StringMod with code, StringMod.from_int(op_kind )
    proc append from StringMod with code, "\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Host-Side Setup Documentation
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_host_setup_comments" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates documentation for host-side OpenCL setup.

    OpenCL host-side setup requires:
    1. Get platform and device
    2. Create context
    3. Create command queue
    4. Compile kernel from source
    5. Create buffers
    6. Set kernel arguments
    7. Enqueue kernel execution
    8. Read results
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate platform/device selection code
    2. Generate context/queue creation
    3. Generate kernel compilation
    4. Generate buffer allocation
    5. Generate kernel execution
    6. Return complete documentation
    @End Implementation

    Let comments be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with comments, "/*\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * Host-side OpenCL setup (C/C++ :\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 1. Get platform and device:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_platform_id platform;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clGetPlatformIDs(1, &platform, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_device_id device;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clGetDeviceIDs(platform, CL_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU, 1, &device, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 2. Create context and command queue:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_context context = clCreateContext(NULL, 1, &device, NULL, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_command_queue queue = clCreateCommandQueue(context, device, 0, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 3. Compile kernel:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_program program = clCreateProgramWithSource(context, 1, &kernelSource, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clBuildProgram(program, 1, &device, NULL, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_kernel kernel = clCreateKernel(program, \""
    proc append from StringMod with comments, kernel_name
    proc append from StringMod with comments, "\", NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 4. Create buffers:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_mem inputBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_READ_ONLY, dataSize, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_mem outputBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_WRITE_ONLY, dataSize, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    cl_mem localBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_READ_WRITE, localSize, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 5. Copy data to device:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clEnqueueWriteBuffer(queue, inputBuffer, CL_TRUE, 0, dataSize, hostInput, 0, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 6. Set kernel arguments:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 0, sizeof(cl_mem , &inputBuffer);\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 1, sizeof(cl_mem , &outputBuffer);\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 2, 256 * sizeof(float , NULL); // Local memory\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 3, sizeof(int , &size);\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 7. Execute kernel:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    size_t globalSize = (size + 255 / 256 * 256;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    size_t localSize = 256;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clEnqueueNDRangeKernel(queue, kernel, 1, NULL, &globalSize, &localSize, 0, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 8. Read results:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clEnqueueReadBuffer(queue, outputBuffer, CL_TRUE, 0, dataSize, hostOutput, 0, NULL, NULL ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " * 9. Cleanup:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clReleaseMemObject(inputBuffer ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clReleaseMemObject(outputBuffer ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clReleaseKernel(kernel ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clReleaseProgram(program ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clReleaseCommandQueue(queue ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " *    clReleaseContext(context ;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with comments, " */\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with comments
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Mapping
Note: ================================================================

Process called "map_bifrost_type_to_opencl" that takes bifrost_type as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Maps Bifrost types to OpenCL types.

    Mappings:
    - Primitive INT8 → char
    - Primitive INT32 → int
    - Primitive FLOAT32 → float
    - Primitive FLOAT64 → double
    - Vector<float, 2> → float2
    - Vector<float, 4> → float4
    - Vector<float, 8> → float8
    - Vector<float, 16> → float16
    - Matrix → float* (pointer)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get type discriminant
    2. Map to appropriate OpenCL type
    3. Return OpenCL type string
    @End Implementation

    If bifrost_type equals 0:
        Return "void"
    End If

    Let discriminant be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 0

    Note: Primitive types
    If discriminant equals 0:
        Let prim_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 8

        Note: INT8=0, INT16=1, INT32=2, INT64=3
        If prim_kind equals 0:
            Return "char"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 1:
            Return "short"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 2:
            Return "int"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 3:
            Return "long"
        End If

        Note: FLOAT32=6, FLOAT64=7
        If prim_kind equals 6:
            Return "float"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 7:
            Return "double"
        End If

        Return "int"
    End If

    Note: Vector types
    If discriminant equals 2:
        Let element_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 8
        Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with bifrost_type, 16

        Note: OpenCL vector types: float2, float4, float8, float16
        Let elem_opencl be map_primitive_to_opencl(element_type)

        If size equals 2:
            Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_opencl, "2"
        End If
        If size equals 3:
            Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_opencl, "3"
        End If
        If size equals 4:
            Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_opencl, "4"
        End If
        If size equals 8:
            Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_opencl, "8"
        End If
        If size equals 16:
            Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_opencl, "16"
        End If

        Note: Other sizes use pointers
        Return proc concat from StringMod with elem_opencl, "*"
    End If

    Note: Matrix and Tensor types use pointers
    If discriminant equals 3:
        Return "float*"
    End If
    If discriminant equals 5:
        Return "float*"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

Process called "map_primitive_to_opencl" that takes prim_kind as Integer returns String:
    If prim_kind equals 0:
        Return "char"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 2:
        Return "int"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 6:
        Return "float"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 7:
        Return "double"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ================================================================

Process called "get_input_variable" that takes inputs as Integer, index as Integer, var_names as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Retrieves the OpenCL variable name for an input edge.

    For graph inputs, generates input buffer access: input_N[gid]
    For intermediate values, returns the variable name: var_M
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Check if inputs list is valid
    2. Check if index is in bounds
    3. Get input edge and source node
    4. Look up variable name in dictionary
    5. Return variable name or input buffer access
    @End Implementation

    If inputs equals 0:
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    If index is greater than or equal to proc length from List with inputs:
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    Let input_edge be proc get from List with inputs, index
    Let source_node be proc get_edge_source from Edge with input_edge

    Let var_name be proc get from Dict with var_names, source_node

    If var_name equals 0:
        Return "input_0[gid]"
    End If

    Return var_name
End Process

Process called "generate_opencl_device_query" that takes nothing returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates code to query OpenCL device capabilities.

    Device queries provide:
    - Maximum compute units
    - Maximum work-group size
    - Local memory size
    - Global memory size
    - Device extensions
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate clGetDeviceInfo calls
    2. Query relevant device parameters
    3. Return query code
    @End Implementation

    Let code be proc create from StringMod

    proc append from StringMod with code, "// Query device capabilities:\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "// cl_uint maxComputeUnits;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_MAX_COMPUTE_UNITS, sizeof(maxComputeUnits , &maxComputeUnits, NULL);\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "// size_t maxWorkGroupSize;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_MAX_WORK_GROUP_SIZE, sizeof(maxWorkGroupSize , &maxWorkGroupSize, NULL);\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "// cl_ulong localMemSize;\n"
    proc append from StringMod with code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_LOCAL_MEM_SIZE, sizeof(localMemSize , &localMemSize, NULL);\n"

    Return proc to_string from StringMod with code
End Process
